snippet: American officials said that of the 26-missile volley, four fell in a rural area of northern Iran. Russia and Iran denied the report.

byline.contributor: Helene Cooper reported from Brussels, and Eric Schmitt from Washington. Reporting was contributed by Thomas Erdbrink from Tehran, Andrew E. Kramer from Moscow, and Matthew Rosenberg from Washington.
byline.original: By HELENE COOPER and ERIC SCHMITT

lead_paragraph: American officials said that of the 26-missile volley, four fell in a rural area of northern Iran. Russia and Iran denied the report.

headline.main: Four Syria-Bound Russian Missiles Crashed in Iran, U.S. Officials Say
